  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scaling up of a successful pilot project to improve children&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s reading levels in Western Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project addresses the very poor levels of literacy identified in the primary schools of western Uganda. Based on a pilot project in 2013, funded by Comic Relief, it scales up the activities of the work to now reach a total of seventy five schools, with teacher training, low cost resource production, classroom based activities and the promotion of reading for pleasure. The evaluation of the pilot project showed very positive results in improved reading and writing, and the same methods will now be shared much more widely.</narrative>
  </description>
